<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="23Mar1926"><font color="red">23 March 1926</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): Lewis has published a large book <i>The Art of Being Ruled</i> and in the <i>beau milieu</i> of it is what looks like a very determined onslaught on my offending work if I am to judge by some of the epithets &ldquo;demented&rdquo; &ldquo;stuttering&rdquo; &ldquo;punster&rdquo; &ldquo;squinting&rdquo; etc. I am reading it in order to get at the use of these terms &hellip; I am now going to hear Pound&apos;s friend, M. Tinayre, in a concert. He has a tiptap tanner voarse like <font face="wake">C</font> of old. </div>
